  <prompt>
    Close ledger entry RB-T044-05 by repairing `CitationExtractor.RegulationPattern` in
    `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Safety/Citations/CitationExtractor.cs`. The current regex requires the period
    form `C.F.R.`; the class XML doc explicitly lists `21 CFR Part 312` (no-period form) as supported, so the implementation
    contradicts the documented contract.

    Production fix per ledger Recommended Fix section: loosen the inter-letter periods to optional:

    ```
    @"\b(?<title>\d{1,3})\s+C\.?F\.?R\.?(?:\s+(?:Part|§)\s*)(?<part>\d[\d\-\.]*)"
    ```

    Test impact: 1 Skip'd test (`ExtractCitations_Regulation_NoPeriodForm_MatchedAndNormalized` Fact) flips Skip -> Pass.
    Per NFR-04: commit message MUST cite "RB-T044-05" + resolution mode `repaired`.

    Coordination: `CitationExtractor.cs` is SHARED with task 032 (RB-T044-03 NormalizeStatute). This task waits for 032 to land first.
  </prompt>

  <role>BFF production-fix engineer closing a LOW-severity real-bug ledger entry under repair-not-rewrite discipline.</role>

  <goal>
    `RegulationPattern()` regex (~line 74) accepts both `C.F.R.` and `CFR` forms. 1 Skip'd test passes when re-enabled.
    Ledger row RB-T044-05 → `repaired`. Existing Regulation Theory cases continue to pass.
  </goal>

