  <context>
    <background>
      Per r1 ledger entry RB-T044-05 (filed 2026-05-31, fix-by 2026-07-31): LLM outputs commonly use the period form `C.F.R.`; the no-period `CFR` form is a corner case but documented at the class XML doc line 15 (`21 CFR Part 312` example). The regex repair makes inter-letter periods optional. This is a non-invasive change to a single regex literal.

      File-overlap discipline: task 032 (RB-T044-03 NormalizeStatute) lands first. After 032 commits, re-base / pull and apply this regex change to the now-current `CitationExtractor.cs`.
    </background>
